text:
Why I Quit Microsoft:

I had a directory with perhaps 100 files, and I needed to be rid of half of them, the half ending with .OBJ.

I did this:

DIR *.OBJ

It listed only the files I wanted gone. Cool. I did this:

DEL *.OBJ

And it erased every file in my directory. My yelps of horror and rage brought my manager to my office. “Del deleted all the files in my directory! Not just the ones specified.”

“Yeah, it’s had that bug for years.” My manager chuckled, at my reaction and the idea that files might not be discarded for no reason.

That was the last day I worked at Microsoft. I was employed there for 16 more months, but that was the last day I worked.
